li.p:
To estimate g'(a), we can use

  g'(a) \approx \frac{g(a+h)-g(a-h)}{2h}

for an appropriate choice of h.

At the moment t = 30,
the temperature of the potato is 167.6 degrees;
its temperature is rising at an instaneous rate of 2.605 degrees Fahrenheit per minute;
and the rate at which the temperature is rising is falling
at a rate of 0.0516 degrees Fahrenheit per minute per minute.  Over the minute from t = 30 to t = 31,
we expect the temperature of the potato to rise about 2.605 degrees Fahrenheit and for the rate at which its temperature is increasing to drop by about 0.0516 degrees Fahrenheit per minute.  We expect that F(31) \approx 169.7 degrees Fahrenheit, and F'(31) \approx 2.01343 degrees Fahrenheit per minute.
